  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1941 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The frameless leaflet consists of a collage of four photographs and shows figures in courtly dresses of the eighteenth century. In the forefront a woman who wears a bright wig and a shiny long dress with neckline. In the background and above her a man in a black tailcoat also wearing a wig. Behind him the face of an elder man, below a group of applauding people.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The actor in the tailcoat (Gustav Gründgens) played Wilhelm Friedemann Bach (1710–1784), the eldest son of Johann Sebastian Bach. The film was directed by Traugott Müller and released in 1941.</ab>
